</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="262" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1898,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1934,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Apical disc tetrabasal with large madreporite, other genital plates reduced in size; peristome close to anterior margin, 20–35% of test length away from it; bourrelets only very weakly developed; phyllodes with 2–3 series of pores; peristome pentagonal and laterally elongated (modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1015,1155,2006,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" refString="Smith, A. B. (1995) Late Campanian-Maastrichtian echinoids from the United Arab Emirates - Oman border region. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Geology, 51, 121 - 240." type="journal article" year="1995">Smith, 1995</bibRefCitation>
, p. 190).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="263" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cotteau &amp; Gauthier" authorityYear="1895" box="[331,440,151,176]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[331,440,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Vologesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Szorenyi, 1955" authorityName="Szorenyi" authorityYear="1955" box="[463,789,151,176]" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeolampadidae" genus="Hungaresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[463,594,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Hungaresia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Szorenyi" box="[610,789,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Szorenyi, E. (1955) Bakonyi kreta echinoidek [Echinides cretaces de la Montagne Bakony]. Geologica Hungarica, Series Palaeontologica, 26, 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="1955">Szörényi, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pomel, 1869" authorityName="Pomel" authorityYear="1869" box="[861,1189,151,176]" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeolampadidae" genus="Clypeolampas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,1021,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Clypeolampas</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pomel" box="[1038,1189,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Pomel, A. (1869) Revue des echinodermes et de leur classification pour servir d'introduction a l'etude des fossiles. Deyrolle, Paris, 67 pp." type="book" year="1869">Pomel, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are closely similar; according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[305,459,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Smith, A. B. (1995) Late Campanian-Maastrichtian echinoids from the United Arab Emirates - Oman border region. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Geology, 51, 121 - 240." type="journal article" year="1995">Smith (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, there are few stable characters to differentiate between these genera. For example, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pomel" authorityYear="1869" box="[151,311,223,248]" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeolampadidae" genus="Clypeolampas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,311,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Clypeolampas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szorenyi" authorityYear="1955" box="[366,497,225,248]" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeolampadidae" genus="Hungaresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[366,497,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Hungaresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have subcentrally positioned peristomes, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cotteau &amp; Gauthier" authorityYear="1895" box="[1069,1175,223,248]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1175,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Vologesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is in a more anterior position. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[256,405,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Smith, A. B. (1995) Late Campanian-Maastrichtian echinoids from the United Arab Emirates - Oman border region. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Geology, 51, 121 - 240." type="journal article" year="1995">Smith (1995)</bibRefCitation>
also indicated the peristome to be placed at 20–30% of test length from the anterior border as diagnostic feature in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cotteau &amp; Gauthier" authorityYear="1895" box="[418,527,295,320]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[418,527,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Vologesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These values were based on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lambert, 1911)" authorityName="Lambert" authorityYear="1911" baseAuthorityName="Lambert" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[862,1161,295,320]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="toucasi">
<emphasis box="[862,971,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">V. toucasi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lambert" box="[986,1153,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Lambert, J. (1911) Etude sur les Echinides cretaces de Rennes les Bains et des Corbieres. Bulletin de la Societ d'Etudes scientifiques de l'Aude, 22, 1 - 120." type="journal article" year="1911">Lambert, 1911</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ali, 1989" authorityName="Ali" authorityYear="1989" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="rawdahensis">
<emphasis box="[1216,1386,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">V. rawdahensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ali" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Ali, M. S. M. (1989) Late Cretaceous echinoids from Jebel El Rowdah, Hatta area, U. A. E. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie, Abhandlungen, 177, 393 - 412." type="journal article" year="1989">Ali, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This range can now be extended to 20–35% on the basis of our description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schlüter &amp; Wiese, 2017" authorityName="Schlüter &amp; Wiese" authorityYear="2017" box="[1130,1393,332,357]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="rollingstones" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1130,1393,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Vologesia rollingstones</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="2" pageNumber="263" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, illustrating the position of the peristome to be more variable than previously suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1227,1379,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Smith, A. B. (1995) Late Campanian-Maastrichtian echinoids from the United Arab Emirates - Oman border region. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Geology, 51, 121 - 240." type="journal article" year="1995">Smith (1995)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
The presence of bourrelets (i.e., swollen perioral interambulacral plates) appears to be a more reliable character for differentiating between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pomel" authorityYear="1869" box="[475,635,439,464]" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeolampadidae" genus="Clypeolampas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,635,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Clypeolampas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szorenyi" authorityYear="1955" box="[655,786,441,464]" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeolampadidae" genus="Hungaresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[655,786,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Hungaresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cotteau &amp; Gauthier" authorityYear="1895" box="[852,961,439,464]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[852,961,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Vologesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in the last-named genus bourrelets are missing. Furthermore, aboral pustular granules are present only in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pomel" authorityYear="1869" box="[896,1056,476,501]" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeolampadidae" genus="Clypeolampas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[896,1056,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Clypeolampas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1116,1254,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Smith, A. B. (1995) Late Campanian-Maastrichtian echinoids from the United Arab Emirates - Oman border region. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Geology, 51, 121 - 240." type="journal article" year="1995">Smith, 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Occurrence.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lambert" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[353,550,511,536]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="toucasi">
<emphasis box="[353,550,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">Vologesia toucasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the upper Santonian of Aude, southern France (
<bibRefCitation author="Lambert" box="[1260,1428,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Lambert, J. (1911) Etude sur les Echinides cretaces de Rennes les Bains et des Corbieres. Bulletin de la Societ d'Etudes scientifiques de l'Aude, 22, 1 - 120." type="journal article" year="1911">Lambert, 1911</bibRefCitation>
) and the upper Santonian of south central Pyrenees, Lleida province, north-eastern Spain (Gallem, personal communication), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cotteau &amp; Gauthier" authorityYear="1895" box="[349,454,585,608]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="tataosi">
<emphasis box="[349,454,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">V. tataosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the “Senonian of Louristan, Iran (
<bibRefCitation author="Cotteau" box="[905,1201,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Cotteau, G. &amp; Gauthier, V. (1895) Mission scientifique en Perse par J. de Morgan, tome 3. Etudes geologiques, Partie 2 - Paleontologie: echinides fossiles. E. Leroux, Paris, 142 pp." type="book" year="1895">Cotteau &amp; Gauthier, 1895</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ali" authorityYear="1989" box="[1266,1435,583,608]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinolampadidae" genus="Vologesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cassiduloida" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="rawdahensis">
<emphasis box="[1266,1435,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="263">V. rawdahensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the mid-Maastrichtian of the United Arab Emirates/Oman border region (
<bibRefCitation author="Ali" box="[1035,1146,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="263" refString="Ali, M. S. M. (1989) Late Cretaceous echinoids from Jebel El Rowdah, Hatta area, U. A. E. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie, Abhandlungen, 177, 393 - 412." type="journal article" year="1989">Ali, 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
